      • buildLog

        default FsLogger.LogInfo buildLog(java.lang.Object[] msg,
                                  int stackTraceOffset)
        Builds log info with given message array and trace offset between the log method and this method. For example, calling chain from the default method info(Object...) to this method is: 
             info(Object... messages) -> buildLog(Object[] msg, int stackTraceOffset)
        In this case the stackTraceOffset is 1. And the default implementation of info(Object...) is: 
             default void info(Object... messages) {
         if (getLevel().value() > Level.INFO.value()) {
             return;
         }
         LogInfo logInfo = buildLog(messages, 1);
         writeLog(logInfo);
     }
        参数:
        msg - given message array
        stackTraceOffset - offset between the point where log operation occurs and this method
        返回:
        og info with given message array and trace offset between the log method and this method
        另请参阅:
        FsTrace.findCallerStackTrace(String, String, int)
